<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 24 at 3:23PM MDT  by NWS Pueblo</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of central Otero and
south central Crowley Counties through 400 PM MDT...
At 322 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Manzanola, or 20 miles northwest of La Junta, moving southeast at 15
mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Rocky Ford and Manzanola.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
